# Privacy Policy for Exposed Party Game

**Last Updated: November 27, 2024**

## Quick Summary
- We collect only what's needed to run the game
- All game data stays on your device
- We don't sell or share your data
- No account required
- No ads
- No tracking
- No data stored on servers

## Detailed Privacy Policy

### 1. Introduction
Welcome to Exposed! We're committed to protecting your privacy while providing an entertaining party game experience. This policy explains our data practices in clear, honest terms.

### 2. Who We Are
Exposed is developed and operated by AFLA Games. You can contact us at:
- Email: aflagames@outlook.com
- Developer: AFLA Games
- App Category: Entertainment/Games

### 3. Information We Collect

#### 3.1 Data Stored Locally (on your device only):
- Player names you enter
- Game scores and statistics
- Game preferences
- Previous game history

#### 3.2 System Data:
- Basic crash reports through Apple's standard system
- Anonymous usage statistics via App Store
- Device performance data for game optimization

#### 3.3 What We DON'T Collect:
- Personal identification information
- Location data
- Contact information
- Photos or media
- Microphone data
- Messages or communications
- Browser history
- Device ID or tracking information

### 4. How We Use Your Information

#### 4.1 Game Functionality:
- Store player names for convenience in future games
- Track game progress and scores
- Maintain game settings and preferences

#### 4.2 App Improvement:
- Identify and fix crashes
- Optimize game performance
- Improve user experience

### 5. Data Sharing and Third Parties

#### 5.1 We Do Not:
- Sell your data to anyone
- Share data with third parties
- Use data for advertising
- Track users across apps or websites
- Store data on external servers

#### 5.2 Exceptions:
- If required by law
- To protect legal rights
- With your explicit consent

### 6. Social Sharing Feature

When you use the "Share Results" feature:
- You control what's shared
- Sharing uses your device's native sharing options
- We don't track or store shared content
- We don't access your social media accounts

### 7. Data Security
- All game data remains on your device
- Protected by your device's built-in security
- No server-side storage means no risk of data breaches
- No account credentials to protect

### 8. Children's Privacy
- Our app is not directed at children under 13
- We do not knowingly collect data from children
- No account creation means no age verification needed
- Parents can clear game data through device settings

### 9. Your Rights
You have the right to:
- Clear saved player names
- Reset game statistics
- Control device permissions
- Contact us with concerns
- Request information about your data (though we store none)

### 10. Changes to This Policy
- We'll notify you of significant changes within the app
- Updates will be dated and documented
- Changes won't affect your privacy protection level
- Previous versions available upon request

### 11. Legal Compliance

#### 11.1 App Store Compliance:
- Follows Apple's App Store Review Guidelines
- Adheres to Apple's privacy requirements
- Uses standard iOS privacy protections

#### 11.2 International Compliance:
- GDPR (European Union)
- CCPA (California)
- COPPA (Children's Privacy)
- PIPEDA (Canada)

### 12. Contact Information
For privacy-related questions:
- Email: aflagames@outlook.com
- Response time: Within 48 hours
- Language: English

### 13. Technical Details
Our app:
- Uses local storage only
- Requires minimum iOS version [specify]
- Uses standard iOS frameworks
- No third-party analytics
- No advertising frameworks
- No tracking scripts

### 14. Deletion of Data
To remove all app data:
1. Delete the app from your device
2. Reinstall for a fresh start
3. Or clear data through iOS settings

### 15. Final Notes
We believe in:
- Privacy by design
- Transparency in data practices
- Minimal data collection
- User control over their data

Last Updated: November 27, 2024
Version: 1.0
